# CLAUDE.md — Project Instructions for Claude Code
# Place this file at the root of any project to give Claude project-specific context.

## Project Overview
<!-- Describe what this project does -->
This project is a [brief description].

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15 / React 19
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL + Prisma
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4
- **Testing**: Vitest + Playwright
- **Package Manager**: pnpm

## Architecture
<!-- Describe the key architectural decisions -->
- App Router pattern (not Pages Router)
- Feature-based folder structure (not type-based)
- Repository pattern for data access
- Server Components by default, Client Components when needed

## Development Standards
- All functions must have TypeScript types (no `any`)
- Test coverage must be 80%+ before merging
- Follow Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`, `test:`
- Never commit `.env` files or API keys
- Immutable data patterns — never mutate objects

## Key Commands
```bash
pnpm dev         # Start dev server (http://localhost:3000)
pnpm test        # Run unit + integration tests
pnpm test:e2e    # Run Playwright E2E tests
pnpm build       # Production build
pnpm lint        # ESLint + TypeScript check
pnpm db:push     # Push Prisma schema to database
pnpm db:seed     # Seed the database
```

## Useful Paths
- `src/app/` — Next.js app router pages
- `src/components/` — Shared UI components
- `src/lib/` — Utilities, helpers, constants
- `src/server/` — Server-side logic, DB queries
- `src/types/` — TypeScript type definitions
- `tests/` — Test files mirroring src/ structure
- `prisma/` — Database schema and migrations

## Agent Guidelines
- Run tests before marking any task complete
- Use `pnpm lint` after every code change
- Never use `git push --force` without confirmation
- When debugging, read the error fully before suggesting fixes
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones
- Check MEMORY.md for project-specific patterns learned in past sessions

## MCP Servers Available
- `filesystem` — Read/write any file
- `github` — Create PRs, manage issues
- `memory` — Persistent cross-session notes
- `sequential-thinking` — Structured reasoning
